  "texts": [
    "Although LLMs can generate coherent texts, at the moment they still lack the deep semantic understanding that humans possess.",
    "This limitation manifests in flawed logical reasoning concerning contextual details and maintaining logical consistency.",
    "Additionally, during the training process, model biases can be inherited and learned by the LLMs, resulting in milder ratings.",
    "Notably, their are differences between model versions, as previously indicated in Table 4 and Figure 4, which is surprising given that newer model versions typically outperforms their predecessor in complex tasks, which is expected to bring it closer to human evaluative standards.",
    "These findings highlight the ongoing challenges in aligning LLM assessments with human judgment, particularly in content-heavy criteria."
